node.text:
Ever seen a Veilside RX7 with pop-ups before?!

The "Furious 2000s", the next year in the @meguiars series, a year which could safely be described as the year we saw our favourite cars on the big screen! What's your favourite car of the 2000s I wonder? (A lights up shot is on the way!)

The 2000s marked the launch of the Fast & Furious titles, and as inspiring as the first 2 movies were, the one that had real personal impact to me was Fast & Furious Tokyo Drift believe it or not! 😂
-
-
Given I was already obsessed with Japanese car culture at this time, Tokyo Drift gave me a little insight into this culture I was yet to learn so much about, especially pertaining to the Drift Scene. But most notable was @sungkangsta Veilside RX7. Probably one of the most identifiable movie cars to exist, and in all honesty I didn't even know it was an RX7 after the fact! 

It wasn't my favourite looking car, so I took this opportunity to do some rough concepts in regards to what I'd personally do with the Veilside kit, I've always wanted to bring back some of the original RX7-ness to it, and this is the result! 

Retained the pop-ups mainly, and also altered the rear for use with the stock lights. This is a really rough concept for now, but will post more clear and detailed/polished shots later on!

Was it worth me spending almost 5h cleaning THAT ONE WHEEL?! I think so 😂.

Seriously though, ceramic coat your wheels immediately, don't be like me. (My old rear brakes were so messed up & old the rust had started to get baked onto the wheels everytime i drove in the wet). The @rotiform
LHR-Ms are now somewhat clean again!
-
-

Today! Massive thanks to @dan.rollhard and the whole team for a sweet event! Here are some of my favs, let me know which one takes ya fancy! 😂
